<subSubSection id="E68920119E60A1B97EDD55F6057F08E8" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7A2113714B2295421F64FE5615435D08" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44A31F9C40F3092B3ED1944D2402589C" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">
This genus resembles 
<taxonomicName id="2806DCAA8BDA8B3318E7E9E195A038BD" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Saxinis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Saxinis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Saxinis</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished by the epipleural lobe not well developed and from 
<taxonomicName id="CA57BAE9A49561E30E6E7F4D123CE41B" authority="Monros, 1953" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Temnodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Temnodachrys</taxonomicName>
by the sides of the prothorax curved (strongly convergent towards the head); frons with deep medial pit; and distinct elytral pattern with transverse black bands on reddish base color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8E2AA03222E84792B07D3C53C41D9691" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="76722B40A5FD1C269BBEB059EBA6581D" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D95AE9E89762CFC783C906887CF660D9" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Austral region of Chile and Argentina.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7D3682D18E96EBBF940237345425796A" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="26975824E0BABED56D88ECFB669626C1" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D5AAC229DFE587229859D7B8FB88867" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">
<bibRefCitation id="52795E20F805BE58D0C462D9635DA1EC" author="Monros, F" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterists Bulletin" pageId="61" pageNumber="72" pagination="45 - 50" title="Some corrections in the nomenclature of Clytrinae." volume="7" year="1953 b">
<normalizedToken id="A854024F01E10D8E965976229B194326" originalValue="Monrós">Monros</normalizedToken>
(1953b)
</bibRefCitation>
separated the genera: 
<taxonomicName id="DFA220ED5A5B4E04218A97386E84207A" authority="Moldenke, 1970" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Saxinodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Saxinodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Saxinodachrys</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AE32A5800058592513042F634FC61FDE" authority="Monros, 1944" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cylindrodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindrodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cylindrodachrys</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="6C242798C1D752789E65E108C4CAF0E7" authority="Monros, 1953" authorityName="Monros" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Temnodachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnodachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Temnodachrys</taxonomicName>
, formerly considered within 
<taxonomicName id="BE17B64745A9B290F674E96894DC9C44" authority="Lacordaire, 1847" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dachrys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dachrys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dachrys</taxonomicName>
. Currently monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="83C512D5E8390EF73A1C5319A2382441" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="argentinian species checklist">
